🌐 Distributed Architecture Rationale (English)

    "This project utilizes a distributed architecture to optimize computational resource allocation and ensure real-time response. 
The high-level vision layer (YOLOv8/OpenCV) runs on a Linux host to manage intensive AI tasks. Hardware actuation is delegated to an Arduino Uno for precise, 
non-blocking PWM servo control, while a dedicated ESP32 node handles high-frequency Time-of-Flight (ToF) telemetry via I2C. 
This separation of concerns prevents latency in the perception-action loop, a critical requirement for autonomous robotic manipulation."
